        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Idiopathic copper-associated cirrhosis is a rare copper-overload liver disease characterized by a rapidly progressive liver cirrhosis from the first few years of life leading to hepatic insufficiency and harboring a specific pathological aspect: pericellular fibrosis inflammatory infiltration hepatocyte necrosis absence of steatosis poor regeneration and histochemical copper staining."
        },
